Comment: Technically defined as the non-destructive backspace, which moves the curser bacwards one space, leaving the character that occupies it
Unix Newline, on Windows, reset the cursor to left edge
Eject page from printer, often used to signify page breaks in text files
Windows Line Feed, on Windows, scroll the output buffer up one line
Modern files seldom use this character.
Still used in printer control languages, such as Hewlett-Packard Printer Control Language (PCL)
ASCII Check Mark (in SOME code pages and fonts)
